result.execSummary:
The defendant Keith Culberson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Strangulation and Suffocation [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.235(1).
  • Battery [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 940.19(1).
  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Original Transcript (18 pages) commencing SENTENCING HEARING, AUGUST 27, 2015, received and filed.

Defendant Keith Culberson in court with attorney Hazel Jean Washington.  Defendant Keith Culberson in custody.  Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.    Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law. Statements by each counsel and defendant as to sentencing.  
AS TO COUNT 1:
Court sentenced defendant to serve a Term of Imprisonment of 4 YEARS in the Wisconsin State Prison, consecutive to any other sentence, concurrent with counts 2 & 3; credit for zero days served.  Court ordered 2 YEARS Initial Term Of Confinement and 2 YEARS Extended Supervision.
Court found defendant not eligible for Challenge Incarceration or Earned Release Programs.

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- No further violations of the law.
- Complete batterer's intervention program.
- Attend parenting classes.
- AODA assessment; comply with any treatment.
- Maintain absolute sobriety; random screens.
- Attend treatment and/or counseling as determined.
- No contact with victim during the entire sentence.
- Court approves the use of 3rd party contact for the purposes of child visitation.
- Obtain/maintain employment.
- No contact with firearms.
- Pay all costs, surcharges and supervision fees through collection by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.
AS TO COUNT 2:
Court sentenced defendant to serve 9 months in the House of Corrections, concurrent with counts 1 & 3; credit for zero days served.  
AS TO COUNT 3:
Court sentenced defendant to serve 90 days in the House of Corrections, concurrent with counts 1 & 2; credit for zero days served.

Order to Produce for Sentencing Hearing on Ausust 27, 2015 @ 8:30am Received and Filed

Defendant Keith Culberson in court with Attorney Hazel Jean Washington.  Defendant Keith Culberson in custody.  
Kristin M. Schrank appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

**CASE HEARD BY BRANCH 44 FOR BRANCH 40**

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNTS 1, 2, AND 3:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  On state's motion the Court orders penalty enhancer "Repeater" DISMISSED as to all three counts; the Court amends Information document.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  

Jury trial date of 8-17-15 vacated.  Case adjourned to Branch 40.  Defendant REMANDED into custody at this time.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 27, 2015 at 08:30 am.
